.TH RSCRIPT 1 "2026" "rlang" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
Rscript \- compiled R runtime on the fusevm bytecode VM
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B Rscript
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
[\fIFILE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rlang
runs R programs by lexing and parsing to an AST, lowering to
.B fusevm
bytecode, and executing on a shared bytecode VM with a three-tier Cranelift
JIT. Loops and branches lower to native VM ops; R's vector, attribute, and
S3 semantics are served by a runtime host.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-eval " " \fISRC\fR
Execute a one-liner instead of a file.
.TP
.B \-\-repl
Start the interactive REPL on a persistent host.
.TP
.B \-\-lsp
Speak the Language Server Protocol over stdio.
.TP
.B \-\-dap
Speak the Debug Adapter Protocol over stdio.
.TP
.B \-\-build " " \fIFILE\fR
Ahead-of-time compile the script's bytecode into the on-disk cache.
.TP
.B \-\-dump\-tokens " " \fIFILE\fR
Print the lexer token stream and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-dump\-ast " " \fIFILE\fR
Print the parsed AST and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-disasm " " \fIFILE\fR
Disassemble the lowered fusevm bytecode and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success, 1 on a parse or runtime error (reported to stderr as
.IR "Rscript: <reason>" ).
.SH SEE ALSO
Project: https://github.com/MenkeTechnologies/rlang
